Are mage pets better?  They're certainly more versatile, and do tend to have more hp on average.  And as Fazzy said, they gain the ability to dual-weild a spell group earlier.<br>
<br>
Can mages do more damage than a necro?  Short-term, a lot more... but no one ever claimed necros were great at short-term damage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
To answer the question in the topic of the thread(&quot;who's the best solo artist&quot;), the answer is - it depends.<br>
<br>
All the soloable classes(I'd certainly toss druids into the mix, and wizards and shamen if the players know what they're doing) are exceptionally good, if you know how to play them.  Necros are better in some situations, shamen in others, and mages in others.   It's going to depend a lot on the situation(mob level, resistances, area, etc.) and on your play style.  <br>
<br>
If you like killing a few things quickly then medding up, go with mage, wizard, or druid.  If you like longer kills but less downtime, go necro, shaman, or druid.<br>
<br>
The major weakness of a solo mage, imo, is the lack of ability to efficiently deal with adds.  You can't mez like a necro, you can't snare-kite like a druid, and you can't root park like all the other casters.  It's certainly possible to handle multiple mobs as a mage, but it's not as easy.<br>
<br>
To sum up my probably incoherant ramblings... pick the one that suits your play style <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     If soloing is what you want to do, any of the ones I mentioned are great(as are bards, but you sound new to EQ, and bards can take a good deal of skill to play well)<br>
<br>
