mahes excel at 1 thing many classes have trouble with. killing casters. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwinterbreath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winterbreath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/01 4:32:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.funhouse.ugate.net/everquest/runner.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Necro's solo better than mages in most settings because fearkiting + lich means very little downtime.  If you play a mage solo you better have a stack of good books handy because 90% of your time in game will be spent medding.<br>
<br>
If you truly want to play a solo class, forget mages AND necros and play a bard.  A well played bard in the right setting can kill 5 mobs in the same time a necro or mage kills 1.  It's no contest, Bards are THE BEST outdoor soloists period. <p><P><a href="mailto:winterbreath@shadowstrike.com">Winterbreath</a>, Chaos Mage of Xegony<br>
Seregon, Minstrel of Dischord<br>
<a href="http://www.aei-desis.net/">Aei'Desis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglenfinen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glenfinen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/01 5:11:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> With JBoots/Sow potions - yes at certain levels.<br>
<br>
Without - no.<br>
<br>
Overall it I would give a slight edge to the necro(though I have never played one, just from what I have seen).<br>
<br>
But in groups, mages are MUCH better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufazzywabbithugger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fazzy Wabbithugger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(8/2/01 5:45:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Necro's in groups,</span><hr size=1> I dont know why alot of players says that Necro's arent well liked in groups. Man i love grouping with necro's !! During my 40th level career as a magician i have grouped with a few necro's and gotta say that anyday i'll invite a necro in my group. <br>
<br>
 When your in Wide open areas, think about it.. Necro darkness mob, then fears it... he sends is pet over and we send our pets on the mob !! Warriors, rogues.. Have free target practices !!! If another mobs agros, no problem necro, darkness and fears that mob..<br>
<br>
